# Website Keep-alive using Selenium

Simple Python Selenium app to keep websites active.  
Starts Internet Explorer, opens the configured URL's, and reloads those pages every x minutes. 
 New Windows have to be used with IE due to the selenium driver not being able to get the handle of tabs.  


Build
--------
A Windows Executable can be generated using pyinstaller:  
  ``pip install pyinstaller``  
  ``pyinstaller --onefile --distpath ./ keepalive.py``  


Run
--------
Install Python >=3.6 and run the following:  
  ``python -m pip install -r requirements``  
  ``python keepalive.py``  


Requirements
--------
 - Python 3  
 - Selenium  
 - Selenium driver under drivers/ folder  


